<TEXT>
president corazon aquino said today 
her government would meet conditions set by a swiss court for the 
return of 350 million deposited in switzerland by the late 
president ferdinand marcos 
in a decision made public thursday the swiss supreme court 
ruled the money must be returned as soon as a competent philippine 
criminal court has issued a legally binding verdict in a case 
against marcos and his wife imelda 
the money has been frozen in several swiss banks since march 
1986 
the order set a oneyear deadline for the philippine government 
to complete legal proceedings it said that if no verdict is 
returned within that period swiss banks would end their seizure of 
the assets 
the decision of switzerlands federal supreme court should be 
hailed as a victory for the filipino people mrs aquino said in 
a statement for our part we are confident that we will be able 
to fulfill the conditions within the time frame available 
neither marcos who died in september 1989 nor his widow 
imelda has ever been charged with a criminal offense in the 
philippines because the government feared they would demand their 
right to return from exile and face trial 
but david castro chairman of the presidential commission on 
good government said the government did not have to file criminal 
charges against the marcoses to meet the terms of the swiss order 
castro said a guilty verdict in civil suits for embezzlement 
against the marcoses handed down by an antigraft court would 
satisfy the swiss supreme court requirement 
castro said the philippine supreme court has ruled in the past 
that a civil suit whose penalty is forfeiture of assets was penal 
in nature as in a criminal case 
he said the governments swiss lawyers assured him that this 
formula would satisfy the swiss supreme court the government has 
filed 35 civil cases against the marcoses and their close 
associates in the antigraft court 
in bern however justice ministry spokesman joerg kistler said 
the swiss government has no reason to doubt that the philippines 
will open criminal proceedings in the case 
he said it was clear that criminal proceedings have to be 
conducted and that the accused will have to be granted all the 
rights of defense provided for by the federal constitution and the 
european human rights convention 
marcos and his family fled to hawaii after a popular revolt 
toppled his 20year rule and swept mrs aquino to the presidency 
mrs aquino banned the return of the marcos family citing security 
threats 
the aquino government claims marcos and his associates embezzled 
up to 10 billion but has offered little evidence to substantiate 
that figure 
in the four years since marcos ouster the government has 
managed to retrieve only 400 million mostly from marcos 
associates 
castro said the government expects to find more of marcos 
hidden wealth after it obtains seized bank records which under 
the swiss supreme court ruling can be handed over to the philippine 
government 
