mayors believe that while recreational users in the suburbs may be 
driving the drug problem the most severe crisis is elsewhere 
the worst problems the murder and violence among the kids 
who get into the traffic and the delays for treatment for 
lowincome people who dont have health insurance are in the 
cities said murphy who directs the us conference of mayors 
police policy board 
