<TEXT>
a surge in the number of soviet jews 
immigrating to israel in december will give the jewish state its 
highest monthly total of immigrants in its 42year history an 
israeli official said today 
the influx of 40000 jews this month 35000 of them from the 
soviet union is intensifying a major housing crisis said simha 
dinitz head of the quasigovernmental jewish agency dinitz urged 
the government to take over construction to resolve the crisis 
the pace of immigration has accelerated in recent weeks because 
of increasing uncertainty in the soviet union and better 
transportation arrangements by israel dinitz told a news 
conference 
december will be a record month in the history of immigration 
in israel said dinitz whose agency assists the israeli 
government in transporting and resettling immigrants 
the government expects more than 200000 immigrants this year 
about 90 percent of them soviets the total will be second only to 
1949 when more than 239000 immigrants arrived in the new state 
soviets have been pouring into israel since spring 1989 when 
president mikhail s gorbachevs government eased its policy on 
exit permits 
dinitz said that discussions with newly arrived soviets showed 
that the question of lack of stability the disintegration of the 
soviet system is the thing that worries them most 
in addition he said israel has improved its transport 
arrangements via budapest bucharest and warsaw 
he said the housing crisis was created because the construction 
planned by the government had not been carried out 
dinitz said for example that government budgeted for 45000 
new housing units this year but that only 27000 had been started 
not one of the 15000 planned prefabricated homes has been erected 
he said and only 950 of 30000 mobile homes have been moved into 
place 
he predicted a difficult situation for the next 10 to 12 
months and urged the government should take over construction 
dinitz said he did not believe the newcomers would have to be 
housed in tents as some israeli officials have said instead he 
said israel will have to make use of every available space in 
hotels collective farms army camps and public buildings 
he said israel estimates there are 3 million to 35 million jews 
in the soviet union about 1 million higher than soviet estimates 
and that as many as 22 million could come to israel 
he said more than 200000 have arrived over the past two years 
and that 1 million more already have israeli invitations to 
immigrate 
we are already working on the second million dinitz said 
i think easily another million is in the pipeline provided no 
catastrophe happens 
israel has a total population of 456 million people including 
37 million jews and 840000 israeli arabs the people and 
descendants of the people who stayed within israels boundaries 
when the state was founded in 1948 
