time in prison if he fails in the appeal of his cocaine possession 
conviction and subsequent sixmonth sentence 
if it happens it happens ill do the six months and move 
on barry said quietly not that i like the prospects of it but 
ive learned that i cant change that and i may have to do it 
come out and start again 
how did barrys downfall begin berry his former campaign 
director says i think that he partied a lot drank too much got 
on the dope and did too many crony deals really just fell in with 
the wrong people 
maybe in the future if he stays clean he will learn to pick 
his friends better berry said 
sharon pratt dixons landslide victory in the race to succeed 
barry was seen as a stunning repudiation of the mayor whose love 
for the trappings of power contrasted sharply with dixons pledge 
for a simple nononsense government 
and as dixon prepares to tackle problems that include a massive 
municipal budget deficit record murder rate and other woes barry 
turns his attention from those difficulties to the problem of 
finding a job 
im not anxious about the future im not panicky about it 
said barry who has no firm plans beyond a handful of speaking 
engagements one thing is for sure i wont be sitting on the 
sidelines like a little mayor commenting on everything the new 
administration does 
barrys wife effi moved out of their home with son christopher 
last month after sitting in her husbands trial all summer and 
listening to a lurid string of tales that detailed his alleged drug 
use and womanizing 
