campaign hahn the longestserving supervisor in state history 
made lindsay the countys first black deputy supervisor 
after a decade in that job lindsay was appointed to the vacant 
9th district seat on the city council in 1963 in that job 
representing the downtown financial district chinatown and little 
tokyo he helped push through legislation lifting the citys 
12story building height limit that prompted a boom in highrise 
development that transformed the city 
