<TEXT>
supporters of two rival political 
parties battled with homemade bombs in a dhaka suburb friday 
leaving at least 15 people injured police said 
the clash was the first major outbreak of violence between 
political parties since the ouster of president hussein muhammed 
ershad earlier this month it erupted when the awami league and the 
freedom party held campaign rallies at the same place 
police said both sides exploded homemade bombs during the 
