frankfurt airport bound for iraq 
the international atomic energy agency reviewed iraqs declared 
nuclear facilities in november under the terms of nuclear 
nonproliferation treaty of which iraq is one of 141 signatories 
the agency said it found nothing unexpected 
so far only one arrest has been reported in the scandal the 
director of a bonnbased weapons supplier remains under 
investigation for alleged export violations officials say 
companies in other countries including the united states 
britain switzerland and brazil have also been named in connection 
with suspected iraqi nuclear development 
as allegations mount against german companies so does 
frustration in washington 
we know what the germans are up to said a us senate 
source on condition of anonymity there is only an argument over 
how long it takes before he gets the bomb he referred to iraqs 
saddam 
