on the first secret ballot deputies voted 1089583 for 
yanayev leaving him 31 votes short of the margin needed for 
confirmation parliament election officials recorded 107 
abstentions and invalidated 113 ballots for unspecified reasons 
yanayev needed a simple majority of 1120 votes out of the 2239 
registered members of the parliament 
the total number of deputies attending the session was lower 
