<TEXT>
rescuers drilled a hole in the hull of 
a capsized barge off finland and saved two crew but officials said 
friday that although divers continued to search eight more missing 
men were thought dead 
olli lommi 36 first mate and jouko kosonen 41 chief 
engineer were rescued late thursday after being trapped for nine 
hours in an air pocket in the engine room of the upturned finnish 
vessel finnbaltic 
rescuers working in a snowstorm and heavy winds had redoubled 
their efforts after hearing tapping inside the barge 
the 550foot 15000ton barge including a motorized pusher 
section capsized in rough weather off the southwestern port of 
hanko at about 1 pm on thursday while carrying iron ore between 
finnish ports news reports said it overturned in 10 seconds 
because the barge took on water and the cargo shifted 
strong winds and rain forced rescuers to stop searching late 
thursday but operations resumed after weather conditions improved 
friday morning 
the barge was reported entirely submerged at first but 
officials said it later drifted into shallower water and part of it 
jutted a dozen feet or more above the surface allowing rescuers to 
walk on the hull 
we dont believe anyone else is alive in the pusherbarge but 
we have a dozen or so divers trying to get into the vessel from the 
underneath nils radstedt deputy chief of the hanko coast guard 
said 
the pusherbarge had nine finnish crewmen and a pilot on board 
rescue officials declined to speculate on why the vessel sailed 
in winds of up to 62 mph 
we just dont know and we will leave that upto the special 
investigation committee all we know is that it happened very 
quickly and there was no warning radstedt said in a telephone 
interview 
janeric dahlberg the security chief of fg shipping the barge 
owner said the two survivors said they had sailed in worse 
conditions before this vessel was built to sail in rough seas 
radstedt said heat from the pushers engine helped keep lommi 
and kosonen alive while a snow storm raged outside they were in 
good health when taken to the hanko medical center 
