the government announced a deep 
devaluation of the currency on friday as part of a package of 
economic reforms that it urged parliament to pass to keep the 
fractious federation from falling apart 
premier ante markovic announced the measures in an address to 
both chambers of the federal parliament he said yugoslavias 
survival depended on the successful redirection of the nations 
economy along freemarket lines 
we are at a crucial juncture shall we permit this country to 
be faced with inevitable violence or will we ensure a peaceful 
legal and democratic solution to the crisis by continuing our 
reforms he asked 
markovic asked for a wage freeze in most sectors to help keep 
