lots of caffeine have been the secrets helping her through a time 
highlighted by the movies she made mermaids and edward 
scissorhands one she didnt make the godfather part iii 
and a tattoo on depps right arm that reads winona forever 
when i started out working i made a point of doing one movie a 
year ryder said i was going to have a lot of free time but 
all of a sudden i fell into these movies that i wanted to do i 
went from one character to another without having time to think 
about it you kind of lose identity 
its important to surround yourself with people who have the 
best intentions for you and want the best things for you i have a 
family who are my best friends in the world i have two other close 
friends and i have a boyfriend who is great 
hard as she tries for a normal life without maids and servants 
and limousines most people her age dont have careers dont own 
homes and dont dodge photographers 
but her great appeal as an actress is how easy she is to relate 
to the look of permanent adolescent boredom in beetlejuice or 
the mixture of fear and desire as she comes to terms with sexuality 
in great balls of fire and mermaids 
actors seek a childlike frame of mind an openness to emotions 
that allows them to react spontaneously its easier for ryder she 
has fewer years to lose 
i love movies about children like to kill a mockingbird i 
loved it because it was told in this voice of innocence of purity 
it was so incredibly powerful to me because of that it wasnt just 
an adult trying to write in the eyes of a child i liked my life 
as a dog for the same reason 
most of the fan mail i receive is thanking me for heathers 
ryder says of the hit black comedy about the gruesome revenge of 
teen outsiders i think heathers was the first movie that 
didnt completely patronize teenagers i think they were sick of 
what john hughes was cramming down their throats 
heathers is her favorite film but ryder also loved edward 
scissorhands the romantic fable directed by close friend tom 
burton and mermaids the quirky comedy costarring cher and 
bob hoskins 
more disappointing was welcome home roxy carmichael a 
critical and commercial flop that ryder insists was turned into 
something i couldnt relate to and the godfather part iii 
which the overworked actress dropped out of because of exhaustion 
her role of michael corleones daughter went to sofia coppola who 
has been panned by critics 
i dont regret doing any movie i have ever done she says 
whether or not it was any good or not i got something out of it 
from roxy carmichael i made a really good friend also i learn 
things standing up for yourself lessons in terms of direction 
ryders first name came from a town in her home state of 
minnesota she grew up in san francisco and enjoyed a world of 
bohemian poets communes and old movies 
her father owns a bookstore and served as archivist to leary 
the merry lsd guru of the 1960s her mother makes educational 
films ryder took up acting 
i started at 10 or 11 she said i went to a theater 
school american conservatory theater in san francisco and i was 
just taking classes there it was something i was doing as a hobby 
because i was having trouble in regular school i couldnt make any 
friends so i thought i could meet people more like me 
early roles included lucas 1969 and square dance 
in beetlejuice she played the most alienated of teenagers 
decked out in black robes pulled from the actress own closet and 
was the child bride of dennis quaid in great balls of fire 
based on the life of rock n roller jerry lee lewis 
ryder swears edward scissorhands represents her graduation 
from high school films and she is scheduled to appear as a taxi 
driver in a new movie by mystery train director jim jarmusch 
</TEXT>
