<TEXT>
 
editors note johnny depp a forgotten young tv star largely 
unknown by the moviegoing public has found new popularity thanks 
to his title role in edward scissorhands his costar is also 
his fiance actress winona ryder 
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
once dismissed as a television star with a 
teen following johnny depp is earning new respect this season as 
the cutleryequipped creation of scientist vincent price in 
edward scissorhands 
with his weaponlike hands and scarred pallid face depp has 
been drawing critical praise for his haunting portrayal in tim 
burtons hit fantasy its a far cry from the undercover cop tom 
hanson he played during four seasons of the fox networks 21 jump 
street 
the real johnny depp is a handsome 27yearold with a faint 
stubble of black beard and spiky hair reminiscent of edwards he 
recalls being overwhelmed upon reading the edward scissorhands 
script by caroline thompson 
i had a feeling about the story and the character that i cant 
describe he recalled i knew i had to do it 
i started thinking about the character right away i kept 
thinking of the faces of dogs i had owned the eyes of newborn 
babies pinocchio all the great classics like the hunchback of 
notre dame started coming to me and they all compiled in this big 
mass 
when i first met with tim we talked for two or three hours 
me and tim and denise di novi the producer i think we had similar 
images of the character i saw tims drawings and everything just 
clicked 
burton a former animator for the walt disney co brought his 
unique vision to peewees big adventure beetlejuice and 
batman his drawings helped convey the physical appearance of 
edward but depp had to build a character out of someone who had no 
past he was simply an unfinished creation of vincent price 
i kept thinking of a dog depp theorized dogs have that 
unconditional love if you scold a dog he cowers in a corner as 
soon as you call him back hes there and all is forgotten 
a lot of the things that tim and i talked about was just to 
maintain the purity of the character edward has lived in the attic 
of this mansion for seven years and when he comes into suburbia 
everything was beautiful and fascinating to him 
i got the scissor hands a few months before we started 
shooting i just tried to function normally with these long shears 
normal things like working remote control on the television set 
were just impossible trying to work the tv set manually or turn on 
the cassette player was tough going to the bathroom is something i 
dont want to talk about 
i went to sleep with the hands on woke up and one of them had 
been thrown across the room i nicked myself a few times after a 
while it became second nature 
because edward doesnt say a lot i knew early on that the 
character would rely on gestures when i was finally put into the 
costume and bound up that escalated the ideas i had the feeling 
of being bound up and completely restricted not able to move with 
full capacity the wardrobe the hands and the costume helped a 
lot 
depps love interest in edward scissorhands is winona ryder 
his offscreen sweetheart we had been together for six months 
before we started the movie he said it was kind of a lucky 
coincidence she had already been attached to the project then i 
read it and thought that tim would never want me i was pleasantly 
surprised when he did 
johnny depp was born in owenboro ky and moved to miramar 
fla when he was 6 he came to hollywood in 1983 intending to be 
a rock musician a friend introduced him to an agent and depp was 
cast in a nightmare on elm street he played one of the 
soldiers in platoon then began his fouryear sometimes stormy 
association with 21 jump street 
theres nothing bad i can say about the series he said 
on one level it definitely put me on the map theres not a 
better way to learn than to just do it every day on camera five 
days a week 
ive had no trouble with being typed when you meet me you 
realize im an entirely different person from the character i 
played on television 
</TEXT>
