not long ago yolanda whitaker was just another 
kid growing up among gangs and drugs in southcentral los angeles 
when she walked home from school crips gang members threw rocks at 
her because she lived in a bloods neighborhood 
fast forward five years 
yolanda is now known as yoyo one of the leading female rappers 
to emerge from the decadelong maledominated rap revolution 
shes only 19 and she has just one album to her name but shes 
made enough money to buy her own apartment in hawthorne a quiet 
los angeles suburb light years away from watts 
she also gives women a voice in the macho often misogynistic 
rap industry with such songs as put a lid on it she sends a 
