<TEXT>
american airlines inc says its pilots unreliable 
attendance will force the nations secondlargest carrier to reduce 
its schedule by about 4 percent and lay off some employees 
meanwhile the pilots union has told members to obey a temporary 
restraining order against the tactics that management alleges have 
caused delays and flight cancellations 
the allied pilots association has denied americans charges that 
pilots have been staging sickouts taxiing slowly to waste fuel and 
filing frivolous requests for equipment maintenance 
but a taped message from apa president fred vogel on thursday 
advised pilots not to employ supposedly contrived slowdown 
devices or to call in sick if they are not ill the dallas 
morning news reported 
the apa which represents the fort worthbased carriers 8700 
pilots has been in contract talks since october 1989 the old 
contract expired jan 1 1990 
