may be reaching a cyclical low he said 
silvers value tumbled this year from more than 5 an ounce as 
the economy weakened sliding stock prices and slowing industrial 
output raised concerns about demand for silver from the electronics 
and jewelry industries which together account for about 60 percent 
of silver consumption and the photographic industry which 
represents about 40 percent of silver demand 
a general easing of inflation fears in the second half of the 
year prompted unloading of silver bullion by investors who tend to 
buy precious metals as an inflation hedge 
domestic silver consumption in the coming year is generally 
expected to outpace the supply of newly mined and recycled silver 
but us stockpiles are more than adequate to meet the demand 
the silver institute an industry trade group estimates 1990 
us industrial consumption at 123 million troy ounces the 
commodity exchange reported silver inventories of more than 265 
million ounces as of thursday 
as long as we have comex stocks representing well over two 
years of consumption it is unlikely that we will have a 
sustainable rally in silver prices said painewebber analyst fred 
demler 
