<TEXT>
joseph m long chairman and 
cofounder of longs drug stores and a philanthropist who gave 
millions of dollars to educational and environmental causes has 
died he was 78 
the california native born in covelo in mendocino county died 
thursday night at a walnut creek hospital the company announced on 
friday 
long founded the retail drug store company in 1938 in oakland 
with his brother thomas a director of the walnut creekbased 
company longs now has 14000 employees working in 257 retail drug 
stores in six states california nevada arizona colorado 
alaska and hawaii 
in recent years joseph long wasnt involved in the daytoday 
operations of the store chain one of his four sons robert long 
s president and chief executive officer 
long donated millions of dollars to medical education 
environmental and wildlife causes 
he helped established the joseph m long marine laboratory at 
the university of california at santa cruz with an initial 15 
million donation he also gave 325 million to the university of 
california at san francisco medical center which named a wing of 
its hospital after long 
long also founded the california state park foundation which 
contributed money to wildlife and waterfowl organizations 
